name: exit
description: Terminate the current EScheme session with <integer-exit-code> (defaults to 0).

name: file-read
description: Get the contents of <filename-str> as an EScheme data structure.

name: file-read-string
description: Get the contents of <filename-str> as a string.

name: file-delete!
description: Deletes <filename-str> if it exists. Returns the deletion's success status.

name: load
description: Reads and evaluates <filename-str>'s EScheme contents in the global environment.

name: system
description:
Executes a command (or list of commands), using the environment variable
bindings in <env-var-str-list> (defaults to the current environment), in
the <dir-str> directory (defaults to the current working directory).
Returns a list:
  (<cmd-stdout-str> <cmd-stderr-str> <cmd-exit-code>)
